      %h3 
        Big boots are here for another autumn and winter season

      %p
        There are few things better at this time of year, than getting your wardrobe ready for autumn. It always gives me a great sense of purpose.

      %p
        If you already have a great pair of boots from last season make sure they perfectly match everything you intend to wear this autumn as well as the forthcoming winter season.
        A much loved and well cared for pair of big boots could last you right through to spring, which is great news for you, your wardrobe, and your wallet.

      %p
        If you are new to big boots fashion then it’s important to pick the right ones for you from the start.

      %p
        One of the first things I like to do is put all my summer clothes away, so I can see if I have enough clothes to last me through autumn and winter.
        Once you have removed your summer wardrobe you are ready to start.

      %p
        The next important thing is to see what still fits, what you still like, and what needs replacing.
        Without this information, how are you going to know what you have and what you might still need?
        This will be key to helping you get the right boots to match.
        A mismatch could cost you all the way through autumn and winter.

