      %h2 Your big boots styling

      %h3
        Which colour is right for you and how to style big boots
      
      %p
        Picking the right colour is going to be the make or break of your autumn/winter wardrobe and your big boot purchase.

      %ul
        %li
          Pick a colour carefully – for example you need to know how to wear white boots with your wardrobe if you choose it
        %li
          If you like wearing all black, think about a contrasting or neutral colour that will complement a full black outfit
        %li
          Most colours go well with black, so you are free to be as adventurous as you want when choosing a contrasting colour for your boots
        %li
          Big black boots work well if your wardrobe is full of colours, or of a more varied or neutral shades
        %li
          If you are unsure, try a few different colours on with your most worn outfit and see how you feel and look in them

      %h3 
        What price is right for you

      %p
        Budgets vary and so does quality.
        If you plan to wear your big boots all the time it is best to go for a good strong sole that won’t wear out too quickly, especially if you want it to last a few seasons.

      %p
        Here are some more tips to help you balance price with quality:

      %ul
        %li
          The rest of the boot should also be made of a good quality material, one that you are happy with and that will last throughout winter weather
        %li
          Additional material is also important. Whether it has elasticated, or otherwise do make sure the additional material will withstand the level of use you have planned and the weather you expect
        %li
          Comfort and ease of use is always another great thing to consider
        %li
          You want your big boots to be easy to get on and off, no matter what the time of day or weather or location. Know body wants to be stuck hopping around with one boots still on
        %li
          If it is cold and wet outside you don’t want to come in and be struggling with a big wet boot and cold hands either

      %p
        Make the right choice now and you, your boots, and your wardrobe will have a great few seasons together. 

